<topic template="Default" lasteditedby="rbwinst-pr" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Ruler Format Dialog Box</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Ruler Format Dialog Box</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The top, front, and side views of the model each have a pair of </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="The_Ruler" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Rulers</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> that show the coordinates of the model. If the numbers to be displayed on these </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Rulers</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> become too large or too small, numbers might not be displayed with enough precision. The </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Ruler Format</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box can be used to change the way numbers are displayed on the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Rulers</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. To display the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Ruler Format</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box, either double-click on a </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="The_Ruler" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Ruler</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> or select </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Customize|Ruler Format…</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> To change the way the numbers on a particular </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Ruler</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true"> are displayed</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, change to the tab for that </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Ruler</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and change the precision and decimals in the edit box. To see what effect this will have, type a number in the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Sample number</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> edit box and see how it is displayed in the preview area.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">It is also possible to change the spacing between tick marks (in pixels) by changing the </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Desired tick spacing</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. This value will act as a starting point in determining the increment between adjacent tick marks.</text></para>
  </body>
